snippet.textDisplay:
Tom Cruise is the biggest movie star ever. His longevity will be unrivaled when his career ends.
*Opening weekends: 28 starring movies starred that had #1 weekends at the BO, most since 1960 and possibly of all time
* Box office peak: 7 #1s in the Quigley polls, noone else has more than 5
* BO consistency: tied with Eastwood at 21 years in Quigley top-10 behind only John Wayne's 25 -but Wayne was not quite as big abroad (Since 2013 Quigley stopped publishing these data.)
* Highest worldwide BO for starring non-sequels when adjusted for inflation (2nd to Harrison Ford if we include sequels)
* Most $100m movies as a lead in domestic
* Most $200m movies as a lead in WW
* Still Consistently number 1 in bankability index ( https://m.the-numbers.com/bankability )
Many people complaints that Tom Cruise playing Tom Cruise. I think that's what made him mega star..His box office power is second to none in terms of longevity. I mean look at the WW gross of The Mummy and Jack Reacher 2..Those movies are utter trash...Those box office numbers are purely because of his star power which I don't think anyone can replicate..
His schedule for next 4 years is packed with Top Gun 2, MI 7 & 8, EOT sequel..That's full movie star for 4 years. I think he is doing these action roles before the age catch up with him..
I am curious to see that how he will be transitioning after these movies. He don't necessarily needs to be a great actor. He is a Star..Stars like him and Denzel sells the movie with their charisma not by acting..
The most impressive thing is that inspite of all the bad press, scientology, personal life crisis his career is still intact..I don't think anyone can survived successfully with this much hate other than Tom Cruise.
Personally I don't think its a good idea to work in a superhero movies.. Paramount pretty much allows him to do whatever he wants..Whether its picking/firing co stars, directors, scripts..He will be always movie star till he dies..
